017package org.microbean.qualifier;
018
019import java.lang.constant.MethodHandleDesc;
020import java.lang.constant.MethodTypeDesc;
021
022import java.util.Collection;
023import java.util.Iterator;
024import java.util.List;
025import java.util.Objects;
026import java.util.TreeSet;
027
028import java.util.function.Function;
029
030import static java.lang.constant.ConstantDescs.CD_Collection;
031
032import static java.lang.constant.DirectMethodHandleDesc.Kind.STATIC;
033
034import static org.microbean.qualifier.ConstantDescs.CD_Iterable;
035import static org.microbean.qualifier.ConstantDescs.CD_Qualifiers;
036
037/**
038 * An immutable {@link Bindings} containing {@link Qualifier}
039 * instances.
040 *
041 * <p>This is a <a
042 * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/doc-files/ValueBased.html">value-based</a>
043 * class.</p>
044 *
045 * @param <K> the type of a {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
046 * Qualifier#attributes() attribute keys}
047 *
048 * @param <V> the type of a {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
049 * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
050 *
051 * @author <a href="https://about.me/lairdnelson"
052 * target="_parent">Laird Nelson</a>
053 *
054 * @see Bindings
055 */
056public final class Qualifiers<K extends Comparable<? super K>, V> extends Bindings<K, V, Qualifier<K, V>> {
057
058
059  /*
060   * Static fields.
061   */
062
063
064  private static final Qualifiers<?, ?> EMPTY = new Qualifiers<>(List.of());
065
066
067  /*
068   * Constructors.
069   */
070
071
072  private Qualifiers(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<K, V>> qualifiers) {
073    super(qualifiers);
074  }
075
076
077  /*
078   * Instance methods.
079   */
080
081
082  /**
083   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} with
084   * this {@link Qualifiers}' entries and an additional entry
085   * consisting of the supplied {@link Qualifier}.
086   *
087   * <p>The returned {@link Qualifiers} <strong>will be new</strong>
088   * unless {@code qualifier} is {@code null}, in which case {@code
089   * this} will be returned.</p>
090   *
091   * @param qualifier a {@link Qualifier}; may be {@code null} in
092   * which case {@code this} will be returned
093   *
094   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} with this {@link Qualifiers}'
095   * entries and an additional entry consisting of the supplied {@link
096   * Qualifier}
097   *
098   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
099   *
100   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
101   *
102   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
103   * threads.
104   *
105   * @see #plus(Iterable)
106   */
107  public final Qualifiers<K, V> plus(final Qualifier<K, V> qualifier) {
108    if (qualifier == null) {
109      return this;
110    } else if (this.isEmpty()) {
111      return of(qualifier);
112    } else {
113      return this.plus(List.of(qualifier));
114    }
115  }
116
117  /**
118   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} with
119   * this {@link Qualifiers}' entries and additional entries
120   * represented by the supplied {@code qualifiers}.
121   *
122   * <p>The returned {@link Qualifiers} <strong>will be new</strong>
123   * unless {@code qualifier} is {@code null}, in which case {@code
124   * this} will be returned.</p>
125   *
126   * @param qualifiers additional {@link Qualifier}s; may be {@code
127   * null} in which case {@code this} will be returned
128   *
129   * @return a {@link Qualifiers} with this {@link Qualifiers}'
130   * entries and additional entries represented by the supplied {@code
131   * qualifiers}
132   *
133   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
134   *
135   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
136   *
137   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
138   * threads.
139   */
140  public final Qualifiers<K, V> plus(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<K, V>> qualifiers) {
141    if (qualifiers == null) {
142      return this;
143    } else if (this.isEmpty()) {
144      return of(qualifiers);
145    }
146    final Collection<Qualifier<K, V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
147    for (final Qualifier<K, V> q : this) {
148      newQualifiers.add(q);
149    }
150    for (final Qualifier<K, V> q : qualifiers) {
151      newQualifiers.add(q);
152    }
153    return of(newQualifiers);
154  }
155
156  /**
157   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
158   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
159   * keys} are prefixed with the supplied {@code prefix}.
160   *
161   * <p>If this {@link Qualifiers} is {@linkplain #isEmpty() empty},
162   * then {@code this} is returned.</p>
163   *
164   * @param prefix a prefix; if {@code null} then {@code this} will be returned
165   *
166   * @return a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
167   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
168   * keys} are prefixed with the supplied {@code prefix}
169   *
170   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
171   *
172   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic,
173   * assuming the supplied {@link Function} is.
174   *
175   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
176   * threads
177   */
178  public final Qualifiers<K, V> withPrefix(final String prefix) {
179    if (prefix == null || this.isEmpty()) {
180      return this;
181    }
182    return this.withPrefix(q -> prefix + q.name());
183  }
184
185  /**
186   * Returns a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
187   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
188   * keys} are produced by the supplied {@link Function}, which is
189   * expected to prepend a prefix to the original key and return the
190   * result.
191   *
192   * <p>If this {@link Qualifiers} is {@linkplain #isEmpty() empty},
193   * then {@code this} is returned.</p>
194   *
195   * @param f a deterministic, idempotent {@link Function} that
196   * accepts keys drawn from this {@link Qualifiers}' {@link
197   * Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute keys}
198   * and returns a non-{@code null} prefixed version of that key; may
199   * be {@code null} in which case {@code this} will be returned
200   *
201   * @return a <strong>usually new</strong> {@link Qualifiers} whose
202   * {@link Qualifier}s' {@linkplain Qualifier#attributes() attribute
203   * keys} have been prefixed by the actions of the supplied {@link
204   * Function}
205   *
206   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
207   *
208   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic,
209   * assuming the supplied {@link Function} is.
210   *
211   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
212   * threads, assuming the supplied {@link Function} is
213   */
214  public final Qualifiers<K, V> withPrefix(final Function<? super Qualifier<K, V>, ? extends String> f) {
215    if (f == null || this.isEmpty()) {
216      return this;
217    }
218    final Collection<Qualifier<K, V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
219    for (final Qualifier<K, V> q : this) {
220      newQualifiers.add(Qualifier.of(f.apply(q),
221                                     q.value(),
222                                     q.attributes(),
223                                     q.info()));
224    }
225    return of(newQualifiers);
226  }
227
228  /**
229   * Returns a {@link MethodHandleDesc} describing the constructor or
230   * {@code static} method that will be used to create a <a
231   * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/invoke/package-summary.html#condycon">dynamic
232   * constant</a> representing this {@link Qualifiers}.
233   *
234   * @return a {@link MethodHandleDesc} describing the constructor or
235   * {@code static} method that will be used to create a <a
236   * href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/invoke/package-summary.html#condycon">dynamic
237   * constant</a> representing this {@link Qualifiers}
238   *
239   * @nullability This method does not, and its overrides must not,
240   * return {@code null}.
241   *
242   * @idempotency This method is, and its overrides must be,
243   * idempotent and deterministic.
244   *
245   * @threadsafety This method is, and its overrides must be, safe for
246   * concurrent use by multiple threads.
247   */
248  @Override // Bindings<K, V, Qualifier<K, V>>
249  protected final MethodHandleDesc describeConstructor() {
250    return
251      MethodHandleDesc.ofMethod(STATIC,
252                                CD_Qualifiers,
253                                "of",
254                                MethodTypeDesc.of(CD_Qualifiers, CD_Iterable));
255  }
256
257
258  /*
259   * Static methods.
260   */
261
262
263  /**
264   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
265   * created, whose {@link #isEmpty() isEmpty()} method will return
266   * {@code true}.
267   *
268   * @param <K> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
269   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute keys}
270   *
271   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
272   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
273   *
274   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
275   *
276   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
277   *
278   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
279   *
280   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
281   * threads.
282   */
283  @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
284  public static final <K extends Comparable<? super K>, V> Qualifiers<K, V> of() {
285    return (Qualifiers<K, V>)EMPTY;
286  }
287
288  /**
289   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
290   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
291   *
292   * @param <K> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
293   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute keys}
294   *
295   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
296   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
297   *
298   * @param qualifier the sole {@link Qualifier} the {@link
299   * Qualifiers} will contain; must not be {@code null}
300   *
301   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
302   *
303   * @exception NullPointerException if {@code qualifier} is {@code
304   * null}
305   *
306   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
307   *
308   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
309   *
310   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
311   * threads.
312   */
313  public static final <K extends Comparable<? super K>, V> Qualifiers<K, V> of(final Qualifier<K, V> qualifier) {
314    return of(List.of(Objects.requireNonNull(qualifier, "qualifier")));
315  }
316
317  /**
318   * Returns a {@link Qualifiers}, which may or may not be newly
319   * created, representing the supplied arguments.
320   *
321   * @param <K> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
322   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute keys}
323   *
324   * @param <V> the type of the {@link Qualifier}'s {@linkplain
325   * Qualifier#attributes() attribute values}
326   *
327   * @param qualifiers an {@link Iterable} representing {@link
328   * Qualifier} instances the {@link Qualifiers} will contain; may be
329   * {@code null}
330   *
331   * @return a {@link Qualifiers}
332   *
333   * @nullability This method never returns {@code null}.
334   *
335   * @idempotency This method is idempotent and deterministic.
336   *
337   * @threadsafety This method is safe for concurrent use by multiple
338   * threads.
339   */
340  public static final <K extends Comparable<? super K>, V> Qualifiers<K, V> of(final Iterable<? extends Qualifier<K, V>> qualifiers) {
341    if (qualifiers == null) {
342      return of();
343    }
344    final Iterator<? extends Qualifier<K, V>> i = qualifiers.iterator();
345    if (i.hasNext()) {
346      final Collection<Qualifier<K, V>> newQualifiers = new TreeSet<>();
347      newQualifiers.add(i.next());
348      while (i.hasNext()) {
349        newQualifiers.add(i.next());
350      }
351      return new Qualifiers<>(newQualifiers);
352    }
353    return of();
354  }
355
356}
